Coal shipments from top supplier Indonesia more than tripled to a record 14.5 million tonnes  while imports of coal from Russia nearly doubled to 1.2 million tonnes  Kpler data showed. The imports included thermal  coking  PCI coal and anthracite.Shipments from other top suppliers Australia and South Africa were lower compared with the same period last year but higher compared with imports in May  the Kpler data showed. Imports from the United States fell to the lowest in four months.
